      content: "<div class=\"doc-overlay\" id=\"doc-contract\" onclick=\"if(event.target===this)closeDoc(this)\">\n  <div class=\"doc-window\">\n    <div class=\"doc-topbar\">\n      <div class=\"doc-topbar-dots\"><div class=\"doc-topbar-dot r\"></div><div class=\"doc-topbar-dot y\"></div><div class=\"doc-topbar-dot g\"></div></div>\n      <span class=\"doc-topbar-name\">Ridgeline_Contract_Signed.pdf — Selected Excerpts</span>\n      <button class=\"doc-close-btn\" onclick=\"closeDoc(document.getElementById('doc-contract'))\">✕</button>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"doc-content\">\n      <div class=\"doc-letterhead\">\n        <div><div class=\"doc-logo-name\">Northern Environmental Consulting Group</div><div class=\"doc-logo-sub\">Professional Services Agreement</div></div>\n        <div class=\"doc-ref-block\">Contract No. 2025-NECG-0147<br>Effective: January 6, 2025<br>Project: Ridgeline EA — Northern Corridor</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"doc-h1\">Professional Services Agreement — Selected Excerpts</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-p\">Between <strong>Northern Environmental Consulting Group</strong> (\"Consultant\") and <strong>Northern Corridor Pipeline Ltd.</strong> (\"Client\") for environmental assessment services in connection with the proposed Ridgeline Pipeline Corridor, Alberta.</div>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-h2\">Section 2 — Scope of Services</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">2.1 — Scope</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">The Consultant shall provide a full Environmental and Socio-Economic Assessment for approximately 30 kilometres of proposed pipeline corridor northeast of Grande Prairie, Alberta, as required for submission to the Alberta Energy Regulator (AER). Services include: environmental baseline surveys, geotechnical investigation program, Historical Resources Impact Assessment (HRIA), Traditional Land Use study, First Nations consultation support, hydrotechnical crossing assessments, and a final Integrated Assessment Report.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-h2\">Section 3 — Fees &amp; Payment</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">3.1 — Lump Sum Fee</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">The Client shall pay the Consultant a lump sum fee of <strong>$4,725,000 CAD</strong>, inclusive of all professional fees, subconsultant costs, and a project contingency allowance of <strong>$225,000</strong>. The contingency is held by the Consultant's project manager and is not available for routine scope expenditure without PM authorization.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">3.2 — Milestone Billing &amp; Retainage</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">Invoices shall be issued upon achievement of the milestones below. Retainage of 10% shall be held on all milestone invoices until final written deliverable acceptance by the Client.</div>\n      </div>\n      <table class=\"doc-tbl\">\n        <thead><tr><th>Milestone</th><th>Trigger</th><th class=\"amt\">Amount</th></tr></thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr><td>M1 — Mobilization</td><td>Signed contract + project kickoff complete</td><td class=\"amt\">$472,500</td></tr>\n          <tr><td>M2 — Field Program Complete</td><td>All field surveys and drilling confirmed complete</td><td class=\"amt\">$1,890,000</td></tr>\n          <tr><td>M3 — Draft IA Report</td><td>Client draft issued for review</td><td class=\"amt\">$1,181,250</td></tr>\n          <tr><td>M4 — Final AER Submission</td><td>Regulatory submission filed</td><td class=\"amt\">$708,750</td></tr>\n          <tr><td>M5 — Retainage Release</td><td>Written client acceptance of all deliverables</td><td class=\"amt\">$472,500</td></tr>\n          <tr class=\"total-row\"><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Total Contract Value</strong></td><td class=\"amt\"><strong>$4,725,000</strong></td></tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-h2\">Section 4 — Changed Conditions</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">4.2 — Geotechnical Changed Conditions</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">Where actual subsurface conditions encountered during the geotechnical investigation are <strong>materially different</strong> from those assumed in the Consultant's Methodology Report (the \"Baseline\"), and where such conditions necessitate a material change to the scope, quantity, or methodology of the investigation program, the Consultant shall provide written notice to the Client within five (5) business days of identifying the condition. The Client shall authorize any resulting scope change via written Change Order prior to the Consultant proceeding with additional work. Costs associated with approved changed conditions are recoverable from the Client and shall not be absorbed against the Contract Value or contingency.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"doc-highlight-box\">⚠ <strong>Note:</strong> \"Materially different\" requires documentation of both the assumed baseline condition (from the methodology report) and the actual encountered condition. This clause does not apply to minor variations expected within normal site variability.</div>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-h2\">Section 7 — Change Orders</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">7.3 — Authorization Thresholds</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">Change Orders with a value up to <strong>$50,000 CAD</strong> may be authorized in writing by the Client's Project Manager (<strong>Dale Fortis</strong>). Change Orders exceeding $50,000 CAD require written authorization from the Client's Vice President of Projects prior to the Consultant commencing work. The Consultant shall not proceed with out-of-scope work absent written authorization at the applicable threshold.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-h2\">Section 8 — Schedule &amp; Delays</div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">8.1 — Schedule Constraint</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">All vegetation clearing and access construction activities shall be <strong>completed no later than April 1</strong> of the project year, to comply with the Migratory Birds Convention Act (MBCA) breeding season restrictions (April 1 – July 31). This is a hard project constraint.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"doc-clause-box\">\n        <div class=\"clause-num\">8.4 — Client-Caused Delay</div>\n        <div class=\"clause-text\">Where a delay to the Consultant's work is caused by a Client decision, direction, or failure to provide required information or access, and where such delay results in demonstrable additional cost to the Consultant (including remobilization, standby, or rescheduling costs), the Client shall compensate the Consultant for such costs under a Change Order, subject to the authorization thresholds in Section 7.3.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"doc-sig\">\n        <div class=\"doc-sig-block\"><div class=\"doc-sig-line\"></div><div class=\"doc-sig-name\">Sarah Chen, P.Eng. — Project Manager, NECG</div></div>\n        <div class=\"doc-sig-block\"><div class=\"doc-sig-line\"></div><div class=\"doc-sig-name\">Dale Fortis — Project Manager, Northern Corridor Pipeline Ltd.</div></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>",
